Magic Chocolate Ice Cream
  -America's Test Kitchen

1 tsp espresso powder
1 tbsp hot water
4 oz chopped bittersweet
1/2 c condensed sweet milk
1/2 tsp vanilla
pinch of salt
1 1/4 c  cold heavy cream 


Combine espresso and water, let dissolve ~5 min. Add chocolate and milk to mixture, microwave for 1 min, stirring every 10 s. Add vanila and salt, let cool. Whip cream in stand mixer to soft peaks. Add 1/3 of cream, mix into chocolate, fold in remaining with rubber spatula and transfer to airtight container, chill until firm, 6 hrs.

